  "full_text": "A joke chess problem by Bohuslav Sivák, from the Bratislavan newspaper Pravda, Dec. 29, 1972. White can mate in two moves by resorting to a drastic stratagem. What is it?\n\nSelectClick for Answer\n\nPromote the h7 pawn to a black knight! Now Black has only two moves, both of which lead to mate:\n\n1. … Nf7 2. Bf5#\n\n2. … Kh7 2. Nf8#",
